# Coding rules for Go

* Go code should be idiomatic.
* Prioritize code correctness and clarity. Speed and efficiency are secondary priorities unless otherwise specified.
* Do not write organizational comments that summarize the code. Comments should only be written in order to explain "why" the code is written in some way in the case there is a reason that is tricky / non-obvious.
* Prefer implementing functionality in existing files unless it is a new logical component. Avoid creating many small files.
* Never silently discard errors with `_ :=` on fallible operations. Always handle errors appropriately:
  * Wrap errors with additional context that could be useful for debugging.
  * Propagate errors up the stack.

## General guidelines

* Format go code with `make fmt`
* Run linting with `make lint`
* Run all tests with `make test`
* When making changes to the helm chart:
  * Always document new values using `# -- <documentation>` above the value
  * Generate helm documentation automatically using `make helm.docs`
